import React from "react"; const SummarizedView = ({ starting, goal, debt, income, checks }) => { const overall = (starting + income - debt).toFixed(2) const formattedOverall = Number(overall).toLocaleString(); // Step 3 and 4 console.log(formattedOverall); // Output: formatted number with two decimals and thousand separators const remaining = goal - overall const average = Math.round(remaining / (9 - checks)) const hours = (average / 15.50).toFixed(2) return ( <>

Summary:

Starting Balance
${starting.toLocaleString()}
Goal Balance:
${goal.toLocaleString()}
Total Debt:
${debt.toLocaleString()}
Total Income:
${income.toLocaleString()}
Overall Balance:
${formattedOverall}
Total Remaining:
${remaining.toLocaleString()}
Weekly Income Needed
${average.toLocaleString()}
Weekly Hours Needed
{hours.toLocaleString()}
); }; export default SummarizedView;
